The paper deals with the problem of maximizing XOS functions, which is a fundamental problem in algorithmic game theory and has connections to various areas such as combinatorial optimization, information theory, and learning theory. The paper uses techniques from approximation algorithms, computational complexity, and linear programming. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
